# House of Varsha - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values

# ============================================
# GOOGLE SHEETS INTEGRATION (Optional)
# ============================================
# If you want to manage products via Google Sheets, follow these steps:
#
# 1. Create a Google Sheet with these columns (Products Sheet):
#    id | name | price | description | category | sizes | color | code | image | images | colorVariants | featured | details
#
# 2. For SINGLE COLOR products, use:
#    - color: Yellow
#    - image: main-image-url
#    - images: img2-url, img3-url (optional additional images)
#
#    Example row:
#    K001 | Kalamkari Kurti | ₹995 | Pure cotton... | Kurti | M,L,XL,XXL | Yellow | K001 | https://img1.jpg | https://img2.jpg,https://img3.jpg | | true
#
# 3. For MULTIPLE COLORS with different images each, use colorVariants:
#    Format: Color1:img1,img2,img3;Color2:img1,img2;Color3:img1
#
#    Example row:
#    K001 | Kalamkari Kurti | ₹995 | Pure cotton... | Kurti | M,L,XL,XXL | | K001 | | | Yellow:img1.jpg,img2.jpg;Red:img1.jpg,img2.jpg;Blue:img1.jpg | true
#
#    This creates a color picker on the product page with different images for each color!
#
# 4. For images from Google Drive:
#    - Upload image to Google Drive
#    - Right-click > Share > Anyone with link
#    - Copy the link, it will be auto-converted to direct URL
#
# 5. Publish the sheet:
#    - Go to File > Share > Publish to web
#    - Select the sheet tab (e.g., "Products")
#    - Choose "Comma-separated values (.csv)"
#    - Click Publish and copy the URL
#
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_PRODUCTS_URL=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/YOUR_SHEET_ID/pub?gid=0&single=true&output=csv

# ============================================
# SITE SETTINGS SHEET (Optional)
# ============================================
# Create a separate sheet or tab for settings with columns: key, value
#
# Keys:
#   logo            - URL to your logo image
#   logoText        - Brand name (default: House of Varsha)
#   tagline         - Site tagline
#   whatsappNumber  - Your WhatsApp number (without + or spaces, e.g., 917569619390)
#   instagramHandle - Instagram handle (without @)
#   email           - Contact email
#
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_SETTINGS_URL=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/YOUR_SHEET_ID/pub?gid=SETTINGS_TAB_GID&single=true&output=csv
